The paper deals with distributed algorithms, which falls under the category of Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC). The focus is on graph problems, which suggests that it could also belong to the sub-category of Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS). The paper also mentions covering and packing problems, which are often studied in the sub-category of Computational Complexity (cs.CC). The use of algebraic constructions suggests that it could also belong to the sub-category of Graph Theory (cs.GT). Finally, the paper deals with approximation algorithms, which could place it in the sub-category of Numerical Analysis (cs.NA).
